 **Answer: 16952**

**Explanation**

The picture shows the usual “Ulam” square spiral  

```
… 5 4 3 …
… 6 1 2 …
… 7 8 9 …
```

which continues as  

```
37 36 35 34 33 32 31
38 17 16 15 14 13 30
39 18  5  4  3 12 29
40 19  6  1  2 11 28
41 20  7  8  9 10 27
42 21 22 23 24 25 26
43 44 45 46 47 …
```

The spiral is formed by shells:

* shell 0 – just the centre 1,
* shell 1 – the 3×3 ring (numbers 2–9),
* shell 2 – the 5×5 ring (numbers 10–25),
* shell 3 – the 7×7 ring (numbers 26–49), …  

For shell k (k≥1) the side length is  

\[
s = 2k+1,
\]

the largest number in the shell is  

\[
n_{\max}=s^{2}=(2k+1)^{2},
\]

and the smallest number is  

\[
n_{\min}= (2k-1)^{2}+1 .
\]

The numbers in a shell are placed in the order  

\[
\begin{array}{c}
\text{right side }(x=k,\;y=-(k-1)\,\dots\,k),\\
\text{top side }(y=k,\;x=k-1\,\dots\,-k),\\
\text{left side }(x=-k,\;y=k-1\,\dots\,-k),\\
\text{bottom side }(y=-k,\;x=-k+1\,\dots\,k).
\end{array}
\]

The number 2026 lies just after an odd square:

\[
45^{2}=2025,\qquad 2026 = 2025+1 .
\]

Hence 2026 is the **first** cell of shell \(k=23\) (since \(2k-1 = 45\)).  
Its coordinates are \((x,y)=(k,\;-(k-1))=(23,-22)\).

The eight neighbouring cells are

| relative position | coordinates | shell | number |
|-------------------|-------------|-------|--------|
| W | \((k-1,-(k-1))\) | \(k-1\) | \((2k-1)^{2}=2025\) |
| NW | \((k-1,-k)\) | \(k\) | \(4k(k+1)=2208\) |
| N | \((k,-(k-2))\) | \(k\) | \((2k-1)^{2}+2=2027\) |
| NE | \((k+1,-(k-2))\) | \(k+1\) | \((2k+1)^{2}+3=2212\) |
| E | \((k+1,-(k-1))\) | \(k+1\) | \((2k+1)^{2}+2=2211\) |
| SE | \((k+1,-k)\) | \(k+1\) | \((2k+1)^{2}+1=2210\) |
| S | \((k,-k)\) | \(k\) | \((2k+1)^{2}=2209\) |
| SW | \((k-1,-k)\) | \(k\) | \(4k(k+1)=2208\) |

(The numbers for the four corners come from the well‑known formulas for the odd squares.)

Adding them:

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{sum}&=2025+2208+2027+2212+2211+2210+2209+2208\\
&=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

A compact formula for the sum of the neighbours of the first cell of shell \(k\;(k\ge2)\) is  

\[
\boxed{32k^{2}+24},
\]

and for \(k=23\) we obtain \(32\cdot23^{2}+24 = 16952\).

Hence the sum of the eight neighbours of 2026 is **16952**.
